Package BikeSack

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    BikeSack
    The Bike Sack is a complete motorcycle computer instrument and light control solution.
    BooleanInstrument
    The BooleanInstrument Class extends BikeSack's abstract Instrument This class allows for an Instrument with a Boolean value.
    ConsoleDisplay
    ConsoleDisplay draws a text based representation of a motorcycle instrument cluster for the BikeSack system.
    Display
    Abstract class for a BikeSack Display objects.
    GuiDisplay
    Not Complete
    HeadlightInstrument
    Bike Sack HeadlightInstrument Class
    Instrument
    Provides the user-facing representation of the status of a Sensor
    Output
    Output defines an object that will control any of the outputs within the BikeSack motorcycle system.
    RangeInstrument
    RangeInstrument extends BikeSack's abstract Instrument and allows for an instrument with a proportional value.
    Sensor
    The Sensors provide data to the BikeSack system about the current physical state of the motorbike.
    TextualInstrument
    Provides an Instrument which is oriented around displaying text.
    UsageInstrument
    UsageInstrument builds on the TextualInstrument within the BikeSack motorcycle system.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    BikeSack.CONNECTED_OUTPUTS
    The connected outputs
    BikeSack.CONNECTED_SENSORS
    The connected sensors
    BikeSack.INSTRUMENTS
    The connected instruments
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    SensorException
    Exception that is thrown when the Sensor is set to an invalid value
